bxc3 f5 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 b6 8. O-O Bb7 {transposing to the game.})
1... e6 2. c4 b6 3. Nc3 Bb7 4. e3 Bb4 5. Nf3 f5 6. Bd3 Nf6 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3
O-O 9. Nd2 d6 10. f3 {You will see this plan white often. White wants to go
for e3-e4 in the most direct way.} Qe8 {[%cal Bb8d7,Be8h5,Be3e4,Bf5e4,Bf3e4,
Be6e5] Black goes for the classical plan which was also employed by Vallejo.} (
{In this position, I would have seriously considered} 10... c5 {[%cal Bb8c6,
