b7-b5. At the same time, White should always reckon with ...f7-f5.}) 17. axb3
Qe7 $15 {Despire the premature exchange of the knights, Black keeps a stable
advantage. Eventually, he managed to win the game.} 18. Qd2 Bd7 19. f4 f6 20.
h4 exf4 21. gxf4 f5 22. e5 Qxh4 23. Bd5+ Kh8 24. Qh2 Qxh2+ 25. Kxh2 Rfd8 26.
Bf3 Be8 27. Kg3 Ra6 28. Rfe1 Rb6 29. Ra3 Ne7 30. Na1 a4 31. bxa4 Rxb2 32. a5
Bc6 33. Nb3 h6 34. Rh1 Kg7 35. Nc5 Ra8 36. Ne6+ Kf7 37. Nxd4 Bxf3 38. Kxf3 Rd8
39. Nb5 g5 40. fxg5 hxg5 41. d4 Nc6 42. a6 bxa6 43. Rxa6 Nxe5+ 44. Ke3 Nxc4+
45. Kd3 Ne5+ 46. Kc3 Rxb5 47. dxe5 Rc5+ 48. Kb4 Rxe5 49. Rh7+ Ke8 50. Rg6 Re7
51. Rh8+ Kf7 {0-1 Black wins.} 0-1

