{[%evp 0,64,14,7,15,0,19,14,19,10,23,15,9,6,12,7,14,16,18,6,39,18,26,22,22,0,
34,34,42,-3,13,13,26,26,31,-15,-15,2,2,-73,-42,-74,-62,-58,-13,-16,-22,-62,-84,
-74,-90,-163,-193,-263,-286,-387,-400,-830,-429,-431,-443,-659,-701,-775,-855,
-885,-928] Putting pressure on d6 is a very important idea in the English
Hedgehog. In this example, we shall see how Black should handle it. The
position of interest arises after} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 b6 3. g3 Bb7 4. Bg2 e6 5.
O-O Be7 6. Nc3 O-O 7. b3 c5 8. d4 cxd4 9. Qxd4 d6 10. Ba3 {Immediately putting
pressure on d6. The next move is going to be Rfd1. As a rule of thumb,
whenever White plays Ba3, you should be able to respond with the maneuver ...
Na6-c5.} Na6 $1 {[%cal Ga6c5]} 11. Rfd1 Nc5 {Remember this thematic reaction.
The a3-bishop is completely neutralized now. Black can keep playing in the
typical Hedgehog style.} 12. Rac1 a6 13. b4 {In this structure, the advance
b3-b4 is usually a bit commital in view of the vulnerable c4-pawn.} ({More
solid would have been} 13. Bb2) 13... Ncd7 14. Bb2 Qb8 {[%cal Gf8c8] Another
very precise move. Black wants to follow with ...Rc8, thus putting pressure on
c4. Additionally, from b8 the queen supports the advance ...b6-b5. White does
not have constructive plan in this position.} 15. Nd2 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Rc8 17. f3
({A typical response to} 17. Nde4 {would be} Ne8 {when White cannot increase
the pressure on d6. At the same time, Black will keep preparing the thematic ..
.b6-b5.}) 17... b5 $1 {Now, this advance works extremely well.} 18. cxb5 axb5 {
[%cal Gd7e5,Ge5c4] Black is already better in view of the vulnerable c4-square.
We can now understand the main drawback of the advance b3-b4. Black is already
better and he managed to convert his advantage into a full point.} 19. Qd3 Ne5
20. Qxb5 Qa7 $1 {[%csl Rb5][%cal Gc8b8]} (20... Qxb5 21. Nxb5 Rcb8 $15) 21. e4
Qe3 $5 (21... Rcb8 22. Qe2 Rxb4) 22. Qf1 g5 $1 {planning g4 followed by Nd3} (
22... Nd3 $2 23. Nc4) 23. Rc2 $2 ({Better would have been} 23. a3 {when the
following line is possible -} g4 24. f4 Nd3 25. Nc4 Qf3+ 26. Qxf3 gxf3+ 27.
Kxf3 Nxc1 28. Nb6 Rxc3+ (28... Nb3 29. Nxa8 Rxa8 30. Rd3 $44) 29. Bxc3 Rxa3 30.
Rxc1 d5 31. Ke2 Nxe4 32. Bd4 Bf6 33. Bxf6 Nxf6 $132) 23... Rxa2 $1 24. Nd5 Rxc2
$1 25. Nxe3 Rcxb2 {[%cal Gb2g2]} 26. Qe2 g4 27. f4 (27. Nxg4 Nfxg4 28. fxg4 Bg5
$19) 27... Nxe4 28. Nef1 Nxd2 29. Rxd2 Rxd2 30. Nxd2 Nf3 31. Qc4 Rxd2+ 32. Kf1
Bf6 {[%cal Gf6d4] 0-1 Miles, A (2560)-Adorjan, A (2525)/Riga 1979/IZT} *

