{[%csl Be3][%cal Be4e3,Bd6d5] The Hedgehog is a structure that is closely
related to the endgame. Therefore, studying the typical endgame ideas and
patterns will enable you to play better in the middlegame positions. You will
know what each side is aiming for. Generally speaking, Hedgehog endgames tend
to be favourable for Black. This is because after multiple exchanges, White's
space advantage is no longer an asset. Very often, Black can make use of
White's overextended position. Nevertheless, in this lecture, we will examine
a couple of cases when the endgame is actually favourable for White. On the
diagram, you can see the classical Hedgehog structure with a pawn on e4.
Nevertheless, the white pawn can be on e2 or e3 as well. In this lecture, I
examine the following ideas: 1) The advance ...b6-b5 2) The advance ...d6-d5 3)
Symmetrical Endgames arising after the exchange of the pawns on d6 and c4 4)
Positions with doubled pawns on e6 and e5 5) The advance e4-e5 At the end of
the PGN version of the lecture, you can try to solve some instructive
exercices. I am sure that after studying the typical endgame positions, you
will get a deeper understanding of the Hedgehog structure. Enjoy!}  *

