{[%evp 0,140,37,20,20,-8,12,11,11,7,7,14,40,33,35,3,-4,-7,14,21,30,19,52,22,8,
-45,-26,-66,-71,-88,-26,-19,-36,-56,-63,-83,-80,-93,-79,-89,-83,-106,-99,-94,
-110,-186,-190,-213,-229,-240,-250,-246,-236,-231,-230,-242,-233,-308,-248,
-403,-380,-315,-318,-316,-249,-338,-317,-327,-329,-330,-330,-328,-247,-299,
-302,-316,-333,-373,-364,-418,-312,-418,-424,-388,-402,-402,-372,-395,-307,
-333,-327,-354,-354,-333,-376,-354,-348,-372,-372,-372,-401,-399,-416,-417,
-346,-617,-630,-642,-642,-649,-670,-1152,-1196,-1255,-1402,-1402,-1954,-28075,
-29986,-29979,-29980,-29987,-29982,-29983,-29984,-29985,-29986,-29987,-29988,
-29989,-29990,-29991,-29992,-29995,-29994,-29995,-29996,-29997,-29996,-29997,
-29998,-29999,-30000] Let's take a very brief look at another example from my
online practice.} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 b6 3. Bg2 Bb7 4. d3 e6 5. e4 c5 6. O-O d6 7.
Nfd2 {[%cal Gf2f4,Gg3g4] This is a very typical way of handling the position.
White can also retreat his knight to e1 or even g5. The idea is to start
advancing the kingside pawns by means of f2-f4 followed by g3-g4-g5. Our plan
remains always the same. We will proceed with ...Nc6 followed by ...Qd7, and ..
.0-0-0. After doing so, we will focus on the kingside.} Nc6 8. Nc3 Be7 9. f4
Qd7 10. g4 O-O-O {This is the right setup. Our king is perfectly safe here.
Now, we are interested in opening the kingside.} 11. g5 {This move is already
slightly dubious since Black can strike with ...h7-h6, thus activating the
h8-rook. The following couple of moves are quite logical.} Ne8 12. Ne2 h6 13.
h4 hxg5 14. hxg5 f5 $15 {[%csl Bg1][%cal Bg7g6,Be8g7,Bh8h7,Bd8h8,Be6e5] This
is a thematic way of fighting against White's space advantage. Black is ready
to proceed with ...g7-g6 followed by ...Ng7, and eventually ...e6-e5. White
already has practical problems in view of his vulnerable king. In the end, I
managed to win this game.} 15. exf5 exf5 16. Ng3 g6 17. c3 Nc7 18. Nf3 Rh7 19.
Bd2 Rdh8 20. Qe2 d5 21. Rae1 Bd6 22. d4 Ba6 23. Qf2 Bxf1 24. Nxf1 Ne6 25. Ne5
Bxe5 26. dxe5 Rh4 27. b4 Ne7 28. bxc5 Nxc5 29. Ng3 Nd3 30. Qd4 Nxe1 31. Bxe1
Qc6 32. Bf2 Qc4 33. Qxc4+ dxc4 34. Ne2 Rg4 35. Kf1 Rh2 36. Bf3 Rh3 37. Bxg4
fxg4 38. Ng3 Kd7 39. Kg2 Ke6 40. a4 Nd5 41. Ne2 Nxc3 42. Nd4+ Kd5 43. e6 Ne4
44. e7 Rh8 45. f5 gxf5 46. Nxf5 Nd6 47. Nh6 Re8 48. Nxg4 Rxe7 49. Kf3 Rf7+ 50.
Nf6+ Ke6 51. Bd4 Ne8 52. g6 Rxf6+ 53. Bxf6 Kxf6 54. Ke4 Nd6+ 55. Kd5 c3 56. g7
Kxg7 57. Kxd6 c2 58. Kc6 c1=Q+ 59. Kb7 Qc5 60. Ka6 Qa5+ 61. Kb7 Qxa4 62. Kc7 b5
63. Kb8 b4 64. Kc7 b3 65. Kb7 b2 66. Ka8 Qa5 67. Kb8 b1=Q+ 68. Kc8 Qc2+ 69. Kd7
